=== sw-cor24-rpg-ii Minimal RPG-II Demo (Chain Reselect + 6-Byte Output) ===
Program:
H  control header
F  input file INFIL
I  field 01: A0110  (10-char input slice)
I  field 02: A0810  (3-char input tail slice)
C  REVR01 -> calc stage 0
C  MOVE01 -> calc stage 1 reselects raw field 01
O  DETAIL01 output (10 chars)
O  DETAIL02 output (3 chars)
O  DETAIL03 output (6 chars)

Current boundary:
- Real today: calc slot 1 can now use source selector 01 or 02, so a chained
  program can replace the first calc result with a freshly selected raw field.
- This variant uses REVR01 only to select DETAIL03, then MOVE01 overrides the
  calc result so the emitted 6-byte line is the raw field-01 prefix.

Current runtime-produced output:
RECORD
RECORD
RECORD

Authored source: rpg2.hlasm
Tiny demo source: tiny_rpg_demo_chain_move1_6.src
Generated source: build/rpg2.generated.s
